&lt;p>The goal of integrating an anonymous credential system in &lt;a href="https://ooni.org/install/">OONI Probe&lt;/a> is to increase trust in &lt;a href="https://ooni.org/data/">OONI measurements&lt;/a> by enriching the data with properties about the probes that collected them, while preserving the privacy of our users.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In our &lt;a href="https://ooni.org/post/2025-probe-security-without-identification/">first blog post on the topic&lt;/a>, we explain at a high level what this system is meant to achieve and provide a comprehensive academic literature review of the current state of the art in cryptographic anonymous credential systems.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Probe Security Without Identification</title><link>https://ooni.github.io/post/2025-probe-security-without-identification/</link><pubDate>Thu, 20 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ooni.github.io/post/2025-probe-security-without-identification/</guid><description>&lt;p>Thanks to Toomore Chiang and &lt;a href="https://ooni-research.ocf.tw/">OCF community&lt;/a>, this post is available in &lt;a href="https://ooni-research.ocf.tw/docs/zh-tw/blog/2025/03/2025-probe-security-without-identification/">Mandarin (zh-tw)&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
